{
  "slug": "postgres-swarm",
  "kind": "swarm",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "PostgreSQL",
    "description": "Powerful open-source object-relational database system with over 35 years of active development, known for reliability, feature robustness, and performance.",
    "guide": "## Overview\nPowerful open-source object-relational database system with over 35 years of active development, known for reliability, feature robustness, and performance.\n\n## Prerequisites\n- Decide which Swarm node should host the primary database and make sure the chosen storage path or NFS export is available there before deployment.\n- Choose whether PostgreSQL should be reachable on a published port or kept private on the overlay network.\n- Define the bootstrap database, user, and password up front and store them in your secret management workflow.\n\n## Deploy\n- Render the generated files, review the placement and storage settings, and deploy with `docker stack deploy -c compose.yaml <stack-name>`.\n- Watch the service logs until PostgreSQL finishes initialization and begins accepting connections.\n\n## Post-Install\n- Create any application-specific roles, schemas, and extensions after the primary database is online.\n- Verify backups and at least one restore path before storing real data on the instance.\n- Keep this deployment single-primary unless you add a separate replication or failover design around it.\n\n## References\n- [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/)\n- [Documentation](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/)\n- [GitHub](https://github.com/postgres/postgres)",
    "tags": [],
    "template_version": "18.2",
    "icon": {
      "provider": "selfhst",
      "id": "postgresql"
    },
    "draft": false
  },
  "variables": [
    {
      "title": "General",
      "name": "general",
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "service_name",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Service Name",
          "required": false,
          "default": "postgres",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "postgres"
          },
          "description": "Name of the service."
        },
        {
          "name": "container_hostname",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Container Hostname",
          "required": false,
          "description": "Hostname used inside the container."
        },
        {
          "name": "container_timezone",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Container Timezone",
          "required": false,
          "description": "Timezone used inside the container."
        },
        {
          "name": "postgres_initdb_args",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Postgres Initdb Args",
          "required": false,
          "default": "",
          "description": "Value used for the general settings.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "--data-checksums"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "postgres_host_auth_method",
